tell me construction software companies that offer solutions for this and what type of solutions and whether they implement ai etc for it. and also list how or what kind of dataset/data sources they use for providing this service eg RSMEANS, or EC3 or ICE etc
Several software companies provide specialized tools to help contractors and manufacturers navigate "Buy Clean" regulations through embodied carbon tracking and reporting.
Core Buy Clean Software Solutions
One Click LCA: A leading LCA (Life Cycle Assessment) platform used for Buy Clean compliance (specifically CALGreen).
AI Implementation: Uses AI for automated data mapping to match material quantities from BIM models to its database, as well as an AI Plausibility Checker to flag modeling errors.
Data Sources: It maintains a database of over 300,000‚Äì500,000 verified data points, pulling from global sources including IEA, eGRID, and generic cost datasets.
Autodesk (Construction Cloud/Insight): Offers Sustainability tools that integrate carbon forecasting into the design and construction phases.
AI Implementation: Leverages AI within the Autodesk ecosystem for generative design and early planning to reduce waste.
Data Sources: Integrates directly with the EC3 (Embodied Carbon in Construction Calculator) to import takeoff quantities and forecast emissions.
Locus Technologies (Locus Sustainable Construction): A cloud-based platform specifically designed to track Global Warming Potential (GWP) for materials like steel and concrete.
Solutions: Automatically calculates a project's carbon footprint using material quantities and Environmental Product Declarations (EPDs).
Data Sources: Uses verified EPDs and contractor weight tickets to account for site-specific impacts.
Matrak: Focuses on tracking embodied carbon across supply chains for Buy Clean compliance.
AI Implementation: Uses Matrak AI to automatically calculate Bill of Quantities (BOQ) and carbon data from supplier purchase orders and shipping dockets.
Data Sources: Pulls from EC3, Green Building Council, and live production data from major manufacturing hubs. 
Specialized Tools & Datasets
EC3 (Embodied Carbon in Construction Calculator): A free, open-access tool by Building Transparency that houses a massive database of digital, third-party verified EPDs. It is the primary data source for many commercial platforms like Autodesk and RIB.
Tally / Kaleidoscope: Tally (now part of Building Transparency) provides whole-building LCA data. Kaleidoscope uses Tally data to compare material assemblies like facades and flooring.
Emidot: An AI-powered platform for manufacturers that automates the generation of EPDs by feeding in raw material and energy data, reducing processing time from months to a week.
ICE (Inventory of Carbon and Energy): A commonly cited database used by various LCA tools for cradle-to-gate embodied carbon values, though often integrated into larger platforms like One Click LCA. 




